[BID 1N] With 15 HCP, no five-card suit, and a stopper in every suit, open one notrump — the perfect description.
[POST-AUCTION]
Partner raised to three notrump, so you're looking at about 26 combined points and no major fit. Nine tricks is the goal. This is a textbook hold-up: East holds five hearts to the \HKQ, West only three, and the \HA is your single guard.
[ROLE declarer][STAGE auction-end]
You declare three notrump. East is the danger hand with five hearts to the king-queen; West has three. Plan to duck twice and win the third heart, which strips West.
[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-lead]
A heart comes back at you and your only stopper is the \HA. Duck the first two rounds and take the \HA on the third — by then West, who began with three hearts, has none left. Now drive out the diamond to set up dummy's \DKT987, and if East wins he has no heart partner to reach. Lose the lead only to West, the safe hand.
[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-play]
Two ducks, win the third heart, and West was bare — East's suit was dead. Holding up exactly long enough to exhaust the short hand is the heart of this deal. Cleanly played.
[ROLE leader][STAGE pre-lead]
Lead the \C3, lowest from your longest suit, clubs 9873. With three small there's no honor to lead, so the low card shows your length.
